The '''microchip revolution''' had its beginnings with the inventions of [[integrated circuit]] (IC) and the [[microprocessor]], both of which were developed to increase [[computer]] efficiency. 

This in turn caused the much broader [[digital revolution]], one of the most significant occurrences in the [[history]] of [[humankind]].

