'''''TechRadar''''' is an online publication focused on technology, with editorial teams in the US, UK, Australia and India. It provides news and reviews of tech products and first launched in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Prasant Naidu|title=Times Internet Partners With Future PLC To Bring TechRadar To India|url=http://www.business2community.com/world-news/times-internet-partners-future-plc-bring-techradar-india-0784338#7IbXP1tF4QAphwiU.97|accessdate=18 January 2017|work=B2C|date=19 February 2014}}</ref>

TechRadar is owned by [[Future plc]],<ref>{{cite web|title=TechRadar Boots Revenue|url=https://www.taboola.com/sites/default/files/Techradar%20Case%20Study%20Taboola.pdf|work=Taboola|accessdate=18 January 2017}}</ref> the sixth-largest publisher in the [[United Kingdom]]. In Q4 2017, TechRadar entered the top 100 <ref>https://www.similarweb.com/blog/us-media-ranking-q4-2017</ref> of Similarweb's US Media Publications Rankings as the 93rd biggest media site in the United States.

{{asof|January 2018}}, SimilarWeb reported TechRadar to be the 10th most popular technology site globally with over 73 million readers per month.<ref name="alexa"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.similarweb.com/website/techradar.com|title=Techradar.com Analytics|work=SimilarWeb.com|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.similarweb.com/category/news_and_media/technology_news|title=Top 50 sites in the world for News And Media > Technology News |work=SimilarWeb|accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref>

